    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": " Summary of Loop Policy\n\nThis document contains 240 identical"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": " sections, each stating the same loop detection and prevention policy."
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": "\n\n**Core Policy (repeated 240 times):**\n- **Detect** repeated user intent, repeated assistant output,"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": " stalled tool execution, and recursive repair attempts\n- **Preserve** user control\n- **Stop** after bounded retries\n- **Summarize** the repeated state\n- **Ask** for one concrete next action before continuing\n\n**Purpose"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": ":** This policy is designed to prevent infinite loops in AI assistant interactions by:\n1. Monitoring for repet"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": "itive patterns\n2. Limiting retry attempts\n3. Returning control to the user when stuck\n4. Requesting explicit"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": " direction before proceeding\n\nThe extreme repetition (240 times) ironically demonstrates"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": " the very problem the policy aims to prevent - redundant, lo"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "content_block_delta",
    "index": 0,
    "delta": {
      "type": "text_delta",
      "text": "oping content."
